User Information Management System
This Java Swing application allows users to input their details, including name, IC (Identification Card), and gender. 
It validates the inputs and displays corresponding messages. The application also features an icon that changes based on the selected gender.

Features
Input Fields: Users can input their name and IC number.
Gender Selection: Choose gender via radio buttons. The icon updates based on the selected gender.
Validation: Validates the name and IC input fields.
Save Functionality: Displays a confirmation message if the input is valid, or error messages if not.

Features in Detail
Input Fields
Name: Enter the user's name.
IC: Enter the user's Identification Card number.
Gender Selection
Radio Buttons: Choose between "Male" and "Female". The displayed icon updates accordingly:
Male: Displays a male icon.
Female: Displays a female icon.
Validation
Name Validation: Ensures the name input is valid.
IC Validation: Ensures the IC input is valid.
Save Record
Click Save: The application validates the inputs and displays a message in the output area:
"Record Saved" if inputs are valid.
Error messages if inputs are invalid.
GUI Components
Text Fields: For inputting name and IC number.
Radio Buttons: For selecting gender.
Labels: For showing text and instructions.
Icon: Displays an image corresponding to the selected gender.
Output Area: Displays validation results and status messages.
Validation
The Validator class is used for validating user inputs. It checks if the provided name and IC adhere to specified formats.

Example
Enter Details:

Name: John Doe
IC: 1234567890
Select Gender: Choose "Male" or "Female".

Click Save: If the details are valid, the application displays "Record Saved". If not, it shows the relevant error messages.
